   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The rain roof might consist of multiple parts depending
on system configuration. The rain roof might have top mounted gland
plates. The general procedure is similar for all types of rain roofs.</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Screw on the hexagon standoffs <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b> used to attach
the rain roof <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/Mount_Rain_Roof_Step_1_0000392019.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
                  <note class="- topic/note ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For systems with top mounted gland plates:</b> Fasten the
gland plates with already drilled holes for the cable inlets on the
rain roof, if they are not already attached. Make sure the gland plates
are correctly oriented.</note>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Align and carefully position the rain roof <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b> on
top of the hexagon standoffs <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/Mount_Rain_Roof_Step_2_0000392018.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Fit and screw in the screws <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b> into the hexagon
standoffs <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
